HEADWORD: Bidding
<hw>Bid"ding</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Command; order; a
proclamation or notifying.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Do thou thy master's
<xex>bidding</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or process of making bids; an offer; a
proposal of a price, as at an auction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bidding prayer</ent>⟦br⟧
